Waypoints :
	- clickable
	- take you to the bus stop page
	- get updated from bus positions every 30 seconds
	- on top of the map, so one layer over the map level

Stop/Bus search panel :
	- hidden (?)
	- JTextField to insert bus/stops number
	- JScrollbar to navigate through buses/stops
	- every bus/stop panel clickable
	- every small panel must have a star to add to favourites
	
Busstop panel focus :
	- after the panel in search panel is clicked, this one is opened below
	- the panel must have :
		- bus stop number
		- JScrollBar of next buses with their arrival time
		- every bus has the number of seats displayed
		- the buses are clickable (hopefully) and they will open a bus panel on top of the busstop one

Bus panel focus :
	- after the bus is clicked this one is opened on the same place as the busstop one
	- the panel must have :
		- bus number
		- bus direction (that can be changed)
		- bus stops in that direction
		- current position of the bus

Login Panel :
	- hidden (?)
	- jtextfield for name and password (X)
	- method to check the correctness of them
	- exception to print a message of various types:
		- the user isn't present in the database
		- the password is too short
		- the password is wrong
		- ...
		
Main Frame :
	- every object should be a JPanel
	- it should have positions already set, like the drawing i'm allegating
	- panels MUST NOT be created on top of one another
	- methods :
		...
	- fields :
		...
